This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it proposes a semi-supervised ensemble method to improve generalization ability by using multiple base learners. The method aims to maximize the diversity among the base learners on unlabeled data, which is a common problem in machine learning. Additionally, the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) as these fields often involve ensemble learning and semi-supervised learning techniques.
